article.headline: Old Dominion 75, James Madison 58
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Arnaud Dahi scored 14 points to lead four Old Dominion players in double figures Thursday night and the Monarchs beat James Madison 75-58. Alex Loughton added 13 points, Drew Williamson had 12 and Valdas Vasylius 11 for Old Dominion (20-8, 12-5 Colonial Athletic Association). The Monarchs led 41-32 at halftime after shooting 60 percent, and by as many as 23 points in the second half. It was the Monarchs' sixth consecutive victory in the series. James Madison (5-21, 2-15) lost its fourth in a row. The Dukes were led by Daniel Freeman with 15 points and Juwann James with 11. No one else had more than six. Old Dominion put the game away for good with a 10-0 run that made it 64-41 in the second half, and stayed in the top four in the league standings with a week to go. The top four teams get first-round byes in the CAA tournament.
